---
// Repel composition demo
---

<div class="flow flow-space-md">
    <h2>Repel Composition</h2>
    <p>
        The repel composition pushes elements to opposite ends of a container.
        Perfect for headers, navigation, and any layout needing space between
        elements.
    </p>

    <div class="repel">
        <h3>Header Example</h3>
        <nav>
            <a href="#" class="link">Home</a>
            <a href="#" class="link">About</a>
            <a href="#" class="link">Contact</a>
        </nav>
    </div>

    <div class="repel">
        <h3>Card Header</h3>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary">Close</button>
    </div>

    <div class="repel">
        <h3>Form Actions</h3>
        <div class="cluster gap-sm">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary">Cancel</button>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="repel">
        <h3>Status Bar</h3>
        <span class="badge">Online</span>
    </div>
</div>
